cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on the study of information cascades in online social networks, which involves the analysis of social interactions and the spread of information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the structure and modeling of cascades, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). Additionally, the paper explores the social factors that affect cascade growth, which could be relevant to cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
